Beast Rider					TYPE:General				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Nature's Bond ~ Animal Companion,Special Mount,Companion ~ Hunter's Bond																															PRELEVEL:MIN=7						PRERACE:1,Orc,Half-Orc																								DEFINE:SpecialMountLVL|0								DESC:You gain the service of a monstrous companion or mount.																																																																																																																																											BONUS:FOLLOWERS|Animal Companion|-1																	BONUS:VAR|SpecialMountLVL|min(TL,max(var("PaladinLVL")+2,var("AnimalCompanionLVL")+2,var("CavalierMountLVL")+2))							FOLLOWERS:Special Mount|1	COMPANIONLIST:Special Mount|Companion (Elephant),Companion (Dinosaur (Pteranodon)),Companion (Rhinoceros),Companion (Dinosaur (Stegosaurus)),Companion (Dinosaur (Triceratops))																					SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:Select one of the following creature types: elephant, pteranodon, rhinoceros, stegosaurus, or triceratops. Add this creature type to your list of possible animal companions or mounts. When summoning a creature of the selected type to serve as a mount or companion, treat your effective druid level as if it were two levels higher (to a maximum of your character level). If the creature is large enough for you to ride, it gains the combat training general purpose at no cost.
Blood Vengeance				TYPE:General																							!PREALIGN:LG,LN,LE																																			PRERACE:1,Orc,Half-Orc																																				DESC:Seeing an ally fall in combat fills you with a raging and murderous fury.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:Whenever one of your allies is reduced to negative hit points or killed, you may enter a state similar to but less powerful than a barbarian's rage as a free action on your next turn. If you have the rage class feature and are already raging, your morale bonuses to Strength and Constitution increase by +2 for the duration of your rage. If you do not have the rage class feature, or you have no more rage rounds left, this weaker rage gives you all the benefits and penalties of a barbarian's rage, except your morale bonus to Strength and Constitution is only +2. In either case, this state lasts for 4 rounds.
Destroyer's Blessing			TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Rage																																																		PRERACE:1,Orc,Half-Orc																																				DESC:Breaking things adds to your power.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BENEFIT:When you are raging and you succeed at a sunder combat maneuver, you regain 1 round of rage. If the sunder attempt causes the object to gain the broken condition, you heal 1 hit point. You can only gain these benefits once per round.
Ferocious Resolve				TYPE:General				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Orc Ferocity																																																	PRERACE:1,Half-orc										PRESTAT:1,CON=13																								DESC:Your orc heritage allows you to fight on.																																																																																																																									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Ferocity																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.57	BENEFIT:You gain the Ferocity universal monster ability, allowing you to continue fighting at negative hit points. When using this ability, you gain a +2 bonus on Intimidate checks.
Ferocious Summons				TYPE:General																																					PREFEAT:2,Augment Summoning,Spell Focus(Conjuration)																PRERACE:1,Orc,Half-Orc																																				DESC:Your summoned creatures gain your ferocity.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.57	BENEFIT:Creatures you summon gain the ferocity universal monster ability.
Ferocious Tenacity			TYPE:Combat					PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ferocity,Rage																																																	PRERACE:1,Orc,Half-Orc																																				DESC:You spit in the face of death.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.57	BENEFIT:Once per day when raging, if you are hit by an attack that would deal enough hit points of damage to kill you (negative hit points equal to your Constitution score), as an immediate action you may expend 1 or more rounds of rage to negate some of this damage and keep yourself alive. Each round of rage you spend reduces the attack's damage by 1 point, but cannot reduce the damage taken below 1 hit point.
